INSERT INTO "CART_REQUEST_TOOL"."MATERIAL"(MATERIAL_ID, CATALOG_ID, DESCRIPTION, CODE, POPUP, CREATED_USER_ID) VALUES(114,55,'Consultant (E2)\\ Minimum SAP Experience 2-4 Years','49010770','A Consultant is an individual with an academic professional qualification and with at least 4 years of industry or functional skills in specific application area. Consultants gather facts, analyze the client’s business processes and draw conclusions. The Consultant prepares the design of the solution and demonstrates the design to support the findings and conclusions. Contributes by analyzing client’s business processes and performs configuration work and assists clients in testing cycles. Works on one engagement at a time.',1);
INSERT INTO "CART_REQUEST_TOOL"."MATERIAL"(MATERIAL_ID, CATALOG_ID, DESCRIPTION, CODE, POPUP, CREATED_USER_ID) VALUES(115,56,'Senior Consultant / Project Manager (E3)\\ Minimum SAP Experience 3-6 Years','49010771','Senior Consultant:\\ A Senior Consultant is an individual with an academic professional qualification and with at least 6 years of industry or functional skills. Senior Consultant plays a key role on the project team; either running small projects, managing portions of a large project, driving the analysis, process finalization, while resolving process and technical issues. The Senior Consultant performs the role of a Team Lead and ensures high quality service. The Senior Consultant will be involved in preparing the detailed level plan for his/her functional area. Senior Consultants are expected to build strong relationships and solid reputations within the industry and market they serve. Works on more than one engagement at a time.\\  Project Manager:\\ Project Managers demonstrate deep knowledge of project management methodologies and have good working knowledge of specific SAP tools and methodologies. They also demonstrate the ability to coordinate work assignments and project completion, mentor team members in project management practices, and manage the integration of project components. In addition, they have exemplary consulting skills and can deal effectively with difficult client situations and communications. Project Managers can marshal resources, provide effective solutions, and drive results while gaining the confidence and commitment of client and team members. Minimum SAP Experience is 6+ years and typically have completed several phases of the SAP implementation life cycle.',1);
INSERT INTO "CART_REQUEST_TOOL"."MATERIAL"(MATERIAL_ID, CATALOG_ID, DESCRIPTION, CODE, POPUP, CREATED_USER_ID) VALUES(116,57,'Principle Consultant (E4) Minimum SAP Experience 6+ Years','49010772','A Principal Consultant is an individual with an academic professional qualification and with at least 6 years of industry or functional or IT skills. The Principal Consultant is an authority in a SAP specific functional area, leads new service offerings and has a proven track record in project deliveries and/or account management in a complex vendor environment. The Principal Consultant is used to complex, long-term work (several months) with one customer. He creates or creates & leads a new project in a new service line and is able to develop a solution strategy for client’s business needs with SAP offerings. Has the capacity to interact with SAP technical staff, clients and partners. Project Management skills are desirable. Works on more than one engagement at a time.',1);
INSERT INTO "CART_REQUEST_TOOL"."MATERIAL"(MATERIAL_ID, CATALOG_ID, DESCRIPTION, CODE, POPUP, CREATED_USER_ID) VALUES(117,58,'Program Manager / Senior Project Manager / Chief Consultant / Solution Architect (E5)\\ Minimum SAP Experience 8+ years','49010773','Program Manager:\\ A Program Manager is the management focal point between the customer, strategic partners and SAP during implementation and support of global multi-site and multi-project business processes plus solutions. He/she leverages relationships with customer executive management, customer functional directors and partners and supports these in the Business Solution Architect team in defining the customers’ global SAP strategy. The Program Manager ensures program success (budgets, schedules, quality and business value) and manages and mitigates program risks.\\  Senior Project Manager:\\ Due to systems limitations the desciption has been left out.\\  Chief Consultant:\\ Chief Consultants have extensive industry and business knowledge. They have a broad knowledge of business processes, IT strategies and technology with a deep knowledge in SAP solutions and SAP technologies. They possess a blended skill set in technology, infrastructure, business experience and industry experience with the capability to define the strategy to optimize enterprise wide deployment of SAP technology solutions.\\  Solution Architect:\\ Solution Architects are experts with many years of experience in a wide range of industries, IT fields, and specialist fields. They develop strategies that point the way ahead as well as holistic architecture concepts. In particular, solutions architects advise the customer’s decision makers and management. Solution Architects are responsible and accountable for the technical delivery of the project, in the committed schedule with the given scope. The Project Solution Architect translates the business blueprint to architectural /solution design, breakdown use cases and work packages, sets the architectural and solution implementation guidelines for the project, and on-boards the team with the given governance model',1);
INSERT INTO "CART_REQUEST_TOOL"."MATERIAL"(MATERIAL_ID, CATALOG_ID, DESCRIPTION, CODE, POPUP, CREATED_USER_ID) VALUES(118,59,'Appl.Consulting & Support - Fixed Price','49010774','Use this Product only for Managed Services and projects where payment is based on deliverables or milestones as defined in a Statement of Work (SoW). Attach the copy of the SoW and/or a transparent calculation that shows on which unit prices and numbers you calculated the sum !',1);
